column5: That is a great picture! That is one confused grouse, apparently displaying with erect ruff to the woodpecker.

Glad I was able to get a pic of that.That grouse was running around strutting most of the morning as there were 3 females there.Woodpecker just happened to land close to him.Likely not going to see that to soon again.My new cell phone defiantly takes good pics as this was 40+ plus yard out.

The woodpeckers definitely can fill the void during a quiet time. I had a couple of does I watched eating greens off a fallen tree and an opossum walked right under my stand…he sounded just like a buck so it’s funny how animals can fill the quiet woods with sounds.
John, what is your go to fish fry seasoning buddy?

Mainly Wal-Mart bread crumbs and we put some seasoning in with that.Whatcever you like mix it in.I like lemon pepper.Do use a lot of brands.Freind of mine makes and sells fish mix here and its awesome to.Tonight was the Wal-Mart crumbs.
Not probably going to see that again anytime soon
Need some kind of noise in bush
Fried up the last of the October walleyes.Ill keep deer hunting till Eck gets here in a few weeks and eat some fresh fish.
I believe your title has been used before.
All out of Walleye n pike but last night he was 30 minutes behind the doe n yearling I let walk so now I have 2 butchered up n 1 tag left.
Looks like meat on the table for winter rich,way to pile'm up.
Was a nice treat.Hope to be catching some very soon
Saw 6 dead on the side of the road, one a nice buck, driving today from Ankeny Ia to Marion, Ia, about 140 miles. Bill
Got a interesting picture in the blind.Big pleated wood pecker and a ruffed grouse in same pic.Probably once in a lifetime picture.
